 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: align JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse rendering with the shared section model","description":"Align all renderer variants with the same underlying section model so format differences do not create semantic drift. This task exists because alternate renderers are valuable, but only if they remain projections of the same facts.","design":"The work should identify which sections can be faithfully rendered in JSON, TOON, markdown, and terse forms, how section omission is signaled when formats intentionally compress information, how stable ordering survives format changes, and how truncation cues, omission reasons, and compact explanation handles remain explicit instead of being hidden inside formatter-specific behavior. Renderer-specific affordances should remain subordinate to shared semantics.\n\nThis task should reduce duplicated formatting logic that currently smuggles in different ideas of what the system state is.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when alternate renderers are visibly thin projections over the shared section model and when format changes no longer imply semantic changes.","notes":"Renderer diversity is fine; semantic divergence or hidden format-specific truncation is not.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:19.443640478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:11:35.498453374Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["renderers","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:24.180659194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:35.626151138Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:19.443640478Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:32.881728949Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:33.330634468Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:33.782608292Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:34.236529813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:01.942439757Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:34.895463050Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","title":"robot-redesign/surfaces: rationalize targeted inspect surfaces for work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down","description":"Split the inspect-surface work so coordination-heavy drill-down does not stay entangled with session and agent drill-down. This task exists because work backlog, unread mail, reservation conflicts, handoffs, quota pressure, and incidents deserve a distinct operator-facing detail model from session/pane inspection.","design":"The work should define inspect views or modes for work items, coordination state, quota or health state, and incidents, including stable lookup keys, expected detail depth, how invalid or unsupported lookups are reported, and how these views are reached from snapshot and attention. It should also make clear where these detail surfaces stop, how they coordinate with the shared diagnostics flow for evidence, source-health causes, cursor or replay context, and incident reasoning, and why they do not become another dumping ground for raw subsystem output.\n\nThis task intentionally complements the session or agent inspect task instead of replacing it.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when work, coordination, quota, and incident drill-down are coherently defined and backed by the shared runtime projection with stable semantics and focused operator value.","notes":"These inspect surfaces should explain coordination pain and remediation options, not merely restate the summary sections in a more verbose format.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:44.351219027Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:33.602307828Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inspect","robot-redesign","surfaces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:59.664776955Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_