 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.7","title":"robot-redesign/registry: unify capabilities, schema docs, and command metadata","description":"Introduce a shared robot command and section registry that drives capabilities, help text, schema publication, and transport metadata. This epic exists because the current giant flag-dispatch style makes it too easy for implementation, docs, and capabilities to drift apart.","design":"The registry should become the single metadata source for: surface names, section ownership, schema IDs, argument docs, degraded-feature reporting, and output examples. Checked-in JSON schema artifacts should be treated as contract artifacts, not just reflective byproducts.\\n\\nThis keeps the API discoverable and reduces the maintenance cost of adding or changing surfaces.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when capabilities, help/schema output, and command metadata are generated from one shared source of truth and no longer depend on duplicated hand-maintained descriptions.","notes":"The goal is disciplined metadata, not a grand rewrite of Cobra for its own sake.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:11.451562933Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.684690167Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["registry","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:11.451562933Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":319,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the registry exists to prevent drift. If you find yourself editing three places to describe one surface, the registry work is incomplete.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:12Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","title":"robot-redesign/registry: introduce a shared robot command and section registry","description":"Introduce a shared internal registry that defines robot surfaces, sections, payload schema IDs, and related metadata in one place. This task exists because today's giant flag-dispatch style makes it too easy for help, capabilities, schemas, and implementations to drift apart.","design":"The registry should become the authoritative map for surface names, sections, schema identities, transport availability, and high-level purpose. It should support both human-facing help and machine-facing discovery without forcing each surface to hand-maintain parallel metadata structures.\\n\\nThe goal is not indirection for its own sake; it is one source of truth for robot command metadata.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when robot surfaces and their section-level metadata can be declared once and consumed by downstream capabilities/help/schema/parity work.","notes":"The registry is a key anti-drift device. Without it, checked-in schemas will still rot away from the code that claims to expose them.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:20.438006355Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:45:18.847109502Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:45:18.845963346Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["metadata","registry","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:55.292650023Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:55.785488521Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:20.438006355Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata